<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74763d90-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s31102"><num value="31102">§ 31102.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of the corporation are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74763d91-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s31102/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to promote the health, social, educational, vocational, and character development of youth throughout the United States; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74763d92-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s31102/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to receive, invest, and disburse funds and to hold property for the purposes of the corporation.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id74763d93-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1327">112 Stat. 1327</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
